{"article_id":"WKMXLFO8LQwaTpTV","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"A Missouri grand jury","depth":9},{"id":1,"text":"that heard testimony from about 60 witnesses over 70 hours","depth":9},{"id":2,"text":"declined to indict officer Darren Wilson in the shooting death of black teenager Michael Brown ,","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"sparking riots in Ferguson Monday night and protests nationwide .","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"St. Louis County prosecutor Robert McCulloch announced the grand jury ' s decision Monday in an unusual late-night press conference","depth":8},{"id":5,"text":"that decried reporting","depth":9},{"id":6,"text":"that included \" lack of accurate detail , \" inconsistent and conflicting eyewitness accounts and \" interviews on social media . \"","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"The grand jury decided","depth":10},{"id":8,"text":"\" no probable cause exists \"","depth":11},{"id":9,"text":"to bring any charges against Officer Wilson ,","depth":12},{"id":10,"text":"who is white ,","depth":12},{"id":11,"text":"Mr. McCulloch said .","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"\" They are the only people","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"who have heard and examined all of the evidence and all the witnesses , \"","depth":10},{"id":14,"text":"he said of the grand jurors during a 30-minute announcement","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"that panned reporting in the case .","depth":10},{"id":16,"text":"The grand jury of nine whites and three blacks met 25 times over three months","depth":6},{"id":17,"text":"and heard testimony from three medical examiners .","depth":6},{"id":18,"text":"President Obama made a statement from the White House","depth":6},{"id":19,"text":"in which he appealed for calm at almost the exact instant","depth":7},{"id":20,"text":"rioting broke out in Ferguson .","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"SEE ALSO :","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"Analysis :","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"The first Ferguson indictment goes to ... the news media","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"While \" America isn ' t everything","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"it could be ,","depth":11},{"id":26,"text":"\" people must respect","depth":12},{"id":27,"text":"that the decision was the grand jury ' s to make ,","depth":12},{"id":28,"text":"he said .","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"\" We are a nation","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"built on the rule of law \"","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"and \" there ' s never an excuse for violence . \"","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"The Brown family said in a statement","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"released through their attorneys","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"that they were \" profoundly disappointed","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"that the killer of our child will not face the consequences of his actions . \"","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"The family ,","depth":11},{"id":37,"text":"which was informed of the decision earlier Monday ,","depth":11},{"id":38,"text":"also asked","depth":11},{"id":39,"text":"that people \" please keep your protests peaceful , \"","depth":11},{"id":40,"text":"and said","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"\" let ' s not just make noise ;","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"let ' s make a difference . \"","depth":11},{"id":43,"text":"Shortly after the 9 p.m. announcement , authorities released more than 1,000 pages of grand jury documents ,","depth":8},{"id":44,"text":"including Officer Wilson ' s testimony .","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"Officer Wilson told jurors","depth":12},{"id":46,"text":"that he initially encountered Brown and a friend","depth":13},{"id":47,"text":"walking in the street","depth":13},{"id":48,"text":"and ,","depth":12},{"id":49,"text":"when he told them to move to a sidewalk ,","depth":13},{"id":50,"text":"Brown responded with an expletive .","depth":13},{"id":51,"text":"Officer Wilson then noticed","depth":12},{"id":52,"text":"that Brown had a handful of cigars ,","depth":12},{"id":53,"text":"\" and that ' s when it clicked for me , \"","depth":13},{"id":54,"text":"he said ,","depth":13},{"id":55,"text":"referring to a radio report minutes earlier of a robbery at a nearby convenience store .","depth":12},{"id":56,"text":"Officer Wilson said","depth":12},{"id":57,"text":"he asked a dispatcher to send additional police ,","depth":12},{"id":58,"text":"and then backed his vehicle up in front of Brown and his friend .","depth":12},{"id":59,"text":"As he tried to open the door ,","depth":15},{"id":60,"text":"Officer Wilson said","depth":15},{"id":61,"text":"Brown slammed it shut .","depth":14},{"id":62,"text":"The officer said","depth":15},{"id":63,"text":"he pushed Brown with the door","depth":16},{"id":64,"text":"and Brown hit him in the face .","depth":16},{"id":65,"text":"Officer Wilson told grand jurors","depth":18},{"id":66,"text":"he was thinking :","depth":18},{"id":67,"text":"\" What do I do not","depth":18},{"id":68,"text":"to get beaten inside my car . \"","depth":18},{"id":69,"text":"\" I drew my gun , \"","depth":18},{"id":70,"text":"Officer Wilson told the grand jury .","depth":18},{"id":71,"text":"\" I said ,","depth":20},{"id":72,"text":"' Get back","depth":21},{"id":73,"text":"or I ' m going to shoot you . ' \" He immediately grabs my gun","depth":21},{"id":74,"text":"and says ,","depth":21},{"id":75,"text":"' You are too much of a pussy","depth":22},{"id":76,"text":"to shoot me , ' \"","depth":22},{"id":77,"text":"Officer Wilson told grand jurors .","depth":20},{"id":78,"text":"He said","depth":20},{"id":79,"text":"Brown grabbed the gun with his right hand ,","depth":21},{"id":80,"text":"twisted it","depth":22},{"id":81,"text":"and \" digs it into my hip . \"","depth":22},{"id":82,"text":"Asked why he felt the need","depth":21},{"id":83,"text":"to pull his gun ,","depth":21},{"id":84,"text":"Wilson told grand jurors","depth":21},{"id":85,"text":"he was concerned","depth":22},{"id":86,"text":"another punch to his face could \" knock me out or worse . \"","depth":22},{"id":87,"text":"After shots were fired in the vehicle ,","depth":17},{"id":88,"text":"Brown fled","depth":18},{"id":89,"text":"and Officer Wilson gave chase .","depth":18},{"id":90,"text":"At some point , Brown turned around","depth":17},{"id":91,"text":"to face the officer .","depth":17},{"id":92,"text":"Witness accounts were conflicted","depth":14},{"id":93,"text":"about whether Brown walked , stumbled","depth":16},{"id":94,"text":"or charged back toward Officer Wilson","depth":16},{"id":95,"text":"before he was fatally wounded ,","depth":15},{"id":96,"text":"Mr. McCulloch said .","depth":13},{"id":97,"text":"There were also differing accounts","depth":13},{"id":98,"text":"of how or whether Brown ' s hands were raised .","depth":13},{"id":99,"text":"His body fell about 153 feet from Wilson ' s vehicle .","depth":11},{"id":100,"text":"The long-awaited decision was greeted with hundreds of protesters in front of the police station in Ferguson .","depth":9},{"id":101,"text":"But protests in Ferguson quickly turned violent .","depth":12},{"id":102,"text":"Bottles and rocks were being thrown","depth":14},{"id":103,"text":"and some cars overturned","depth":16},{"id":104,"text":"and burned ,","depth":16},{"id":105,"text":"including at least one assault on a police car .","depth":15},{"id":106,"text":"There also were reports of multiple gunshots , a large fight and images of looting .","depth":13},{"id":107,"text":"Police ordered protesters to disperse","depth":13},{"id":108,"text":"and began using tear gas","depth":14},{"id":109,"text":"when some refused .","depth":14},{"id":110,"text":"Protesters said","depth":14},{"id":111,"text":"one woman had a heart attack ,","depth":15},{"id":112,"text":"and then was gassed by police","depth":16},{"id":113,"text":"as others attempted to carry her to safety .","depth":16},{"id":114,"text":"There was no official confirmation of casualties .","depth":13},{"id":115,"text":"Demonstrations broke out around the nation - Times Square , South-Central Los Angeles , and U Street and the White House in Washington , D.C .","depth":10},{"id":116,"text":"Officer Wilson had been in talks with the Ferguson Police Department","depth":6},{"id":117,"text":"about possibly resigning ,","depth":6},{"id":118,"text":"but it is unclear how the grand jury ' s verdict may affect those discussions .","depth":5},{"id":119,"text":"Rep. John Lewis , Georgia Democrat and a civil-rights icon , took to Twitter","depth":9},{"id":120,"text":"to implore people not to resort to violence .","depth":9},{"id":121,"text":"\" I know","depth":12},{"id":122,"text":"this [ is ] hard , \"","depth":12},{"id":123,"text":"he said .","depth":11},{"id":124,"text":"\" I know","depth":11},{"id":125,"text":"this is difficult .","depth":11},{"id":126,"text":"Do not succumb to the temptations of violence .","depth":10},{"id":127,"text":"There is a more powerful way . \"","depth":10},{"id":128,"text":"Likewise , Rep. Emanuel Cleaver , Missouri Democrat , tweeted Monday night","depth":10},{"id":129,"text":"that","depth":10},{"id":130,"text":"\" African-Americans have long believed","depth":10},{"id":131,"text":"that police resort to force incautiously","depth":11},{"id":132,"text":"when dealing with their young men . \"","depth":11},{"id":133,"text":"\" We hear you , \"","depth":11},{"id":134,"text":"he said .","depth":11},{"id":135,"text":"\" And we hurt with you .","depth":10},{"id":136,"text":"All decent Americans , black , white , brown , should also feel the pain of this family , this community . \"","depth":9},{"id":137,"text":"Officer Wilson is still a victim","depth":10},{"id":138,"text":"despite being exonerated of all charges ,","depth":10},{"id":139,"text":"said Ron Hosko , former FBI assistant director .","depth":9},{"id":140,"text":"\" Although he will walk free ,","depth":10},{"id":141,"text":"his life has been forever changed ,","depth":11},{"id":142,"text":"as he has been exploited in a cynical effort","depth":12},{"id":143,"text":"to turn civilians against cops in fulfillment of an anti-law enforcement agenda , \"","depth":12},{"id":144,"text":"said Mr. Hosko ,","depth":10},{"id":145,"text":"who now serves as president of the Law Enforcement Legal Defense Fund .","depth":10},{"id":146,"text":"The grand jury ' s confidential deliberations were likely contentious","depth":11},{"id":147,"text":"because of the nature of the case ,","depth":11},{"id":148,"text":"Mr. Hosko told The .","depth":10},{"id":149,"text":"\" I would suspect strongly","depth":11},{"id":150,"text":"that all the grand juries are not of a like mind on these things , \"","depth":11},{"id":151,"text":"he said .","depth":10},{"id":152,"text":"The prosecutor ' s office said","depth":10},{"id":153,"text":"it would release the information , evidence , and documents in the case .","depth":10},{"id":154,"text":"\" Because of all the attention on it ,","depth":12},{"id":155,"text":"the likelihood is that there will need to be a fair amount of transparency , \"","depth":12},{"id":156,"text":"Mr. Hosko said .","depth":11},{"id":157,"text":"\" Almost inevitably one or more grand jurors will self-identify","depth":11},{"id":158,"text":"and want to tell the story ,","depth":12},{"id":159,"text":"or sell the story . \"","depth":12},{"id":160,"text":"Many of the basic facts of the encounter have been in sharp dispute since the Aug. 9 confrontation .","depth":7},{"id":161,"text":"Officer Wilson ,","depth":12},{"id":162,"text":"backed by national police groups ,","depth":12},{"id":163,"text":"insists","depth":11},{"id":164,"text":"he acted in self-defense","depth":11},{"id":165,"text":"after the much larger Michael Brown assaulted him in his squad car .","depth":11},{"id":166,"text":"Brown ' s defenders note","depth":11},{"id":167,"text":"that he was unarmed","depth":11},{"id":168,"text":"and say","depth":11},{"id":169,"text":"he was not a threat to the white officer","depth":12},{"id":170,"text":"when he was shot .","depth":12},{"id":171,"text":"Angering the largely black community ,","depth":9},{"id":172,"text":"Brown ' s body was left to lie in the street on a hot August day for more than four hours","depth":10},{"id":173,"text":"as investigators searched for forensic evidence","depth":11},{"id":174,"text":"to piece together what happened .","depth":11},{"id":175,"text":"Attorney General Eric H. Holder Jr. visited the St. Louis suburb nine days after the fatal encounter","depth":12},{"id":176,"text":"to talk about the shooting with residents and members of the Brown family .","depth":12},{"id":177,"text":"In a statement","depth":14},{"id":178,"text":"released Monday night ,","depth":14},{"id":179,"text":"Mr. Holder said","depth":13},{"id":180,"text":"a federal investigation into a possible civil-rights case is ongoing","depth":13},{"id":181,"text":"and that they will not be \" prejudging any of the evidence . \"","depth":13},{"id":182,"text":"In his statement earlier , Mr. McCulloch had said","depth":11},{"id":183,"text":"his grand jury had access to all the same evidence","depth":12},{"id":184,"text":"that federal prosecutors would have access to .","depth":12},{"id":185,"text":"Mr. Holder joined Mr. Obama","depth":11},{"id":186,"text":"in calling for peace ,","depth":12},{"id":187,"text":"stating","depth":13},{"id":188,"text":"that violence does not honor the memory of Michael Brown .","depth":13},{"id":189,"text":"\" Michael Brown ' s death was a tragedy , \"","depth":12},{"id":190,"text":"Mr. Holder said .","depth":12},{"id":191,"text":"\" This incident has sparked a national conversation about the need","depth":13},{"id":192,"text":"to ensure confidence between law enforcement and the communities","depth":14},{"id":193,"text":"they protect and serve .","depth":14},{"id":194,"text":"While constructive efforts are underway in Ferguson and communities nationwide ,","depth":13},{"id":195,"text":"far more must be done","depth":14},{"id":196,"text":"to create enduring trust . \"","depth":14},{"id":197,"text":"All sides had been braced for weeks for a possibly violent backlash","depth":10},{"id":198,"text":"as rumors swirled","depth":11},{"id":199,"text":"that the grand jury was poised to act .","depth":11},{"id":200,"text":"Missouri Gov . Jay Nixon , a Democrat , declared a state of emergency last week in anticipation of the verdict ' s announcement","depth":11},{"id":201,"text":"and mobilized the state ' s National Guard","depth":13},{"id":202,"text":"to join local police","depth":13},{"id":203,"text":"in trying to contain rioting and fighting .","depth":12},{"id":204,"text":"The governor appealed again Monday evening for \" peace , restraint and respect \" in reaction to the news .","depth":11},{"id":205,"text":"Churches were set up as safe havens ,","depth":13},{"id":206,"text":"the area ' s most experienced police officers were deployed ,","depth":14},{"id":207,"text":"protest leaders and police were in constant communication ,","depth":15},{"id":208,"text":"and the National Guard was protecting critical infrastructure such as power stations and firehouses","depth":16},{"id":209,"text":"to allow law enforcement personnel to focus on maintaining calm ,","depth":16},{"id":210,"text":"Mr. Nixon said .","depth":12},{"id":211,"text":"Grand juries are supposed to represent the people ,","depth":11},{"id":212,"text":"but details of the Brown case make it difficult to determine","depth":12},{"id":213,"text":"whether the panel lived up to that standard ,","depth":12},{"id":214,"text":"said Steven Platt , a retired circuit court judge in Prince George ' s County .","depth":10},{"id":215,"text":"\" As far as being the voice of the community ,","depth":12},{"id":216,"text":"we don ' t know","depth":13},{"id":217,"text":"who they are or where they are , \"","depth":13},{"id":218,"text":"Mr. Platt said .","depth":11},{"id":219,"text":"\" This community in Ferguson is obviously divided .","depth":11},{"id":220,"text":"Since we don ' t know","depth":13},{"id":221,"text":"who they are ,","depth":13},{"id":222,"text":"we don ' t know","depth":13},{"id":223,"text":"how well they represent that . \"","depth":13},{"id":224,"text":"Mr. Platt said","depth":10},{"id":225,"text":"many people would react","depth":11},{"id":226,"text":"without trying to understand why the grand jury reached its decision .","depth":11},{"id":227,"text":"\" There ' s people","depth":13},{"id":228,"text":"who have already formed an opinion on what the grand jury will do ,","depth":13},{"id":229,"text":"and","depth":13},{"id":230,"text":"if the grand jury doesn ' t do what they want ,","depth":14},{"id":231,"text":"there will probably be an adverse reaction .","depth":14},{"id":232,"text":"Hopefully , it won ' t be a violent reaction , \"","depth":11},{"id":233,"text":"he said .","depth":10},{"id":234,"text":"Racial tensions in Ferguson came to a head in the first days and weeks after the Aug. 9 shooting .","depth":4},{"id":235,"text":"The 18-year-old Brown was walking with a friend","depth":8},{"id":236,"text":"when he was stopped by Officer Wilson .","depth":8},{"id":237,"text":"The most common narrative given","depth":9},{"id":238,"text":"was that Brown and his friend were walking in the street","depth":10},{"id":239,"text":"when Officer Wilson pulled over in his car","depth":11},{"id":240,"text":"to tell them to move onto the sidewalk .","depth":11},{"id":241,"text":"News reports indicate","depth":10},{"id":242,"text":"that the officer was informed sometime during the encounter","depth":11},{"id":243,"text":"that the two teens might have been involved in a grocery store burglary that day .","depth":11},{"id":244,"text":"The teen and the police officer became embroiled in a confrontation ,","depth":10},{"id":245,"text":"and Officer Wilson shot and killed Brown ,","depth":13},{"id":246,"text":"claiming","depth":14},{"id":247,"text":"he acted in self-defense .","depth":14},{"id":248,"text":"But some witnesses said","depth":13},{"id":249,"text":"Brown had his hands above his head","depth":15},{"id":250,"text":"and was not acting in an intimidating manner","depth":15},{"id":251,"text":"when he was shot .","depth":14},{"id":252,"text":"Brown was later found to be unarmed .","depth":11},{"id":253,"text":"The event sparked protests and riots in Ferguson","depth":7},{"id":254,"text":"and set off a national debate about race relations and police tactics .","depth":7},{"id":255,"text":"Protesters in Ferguson took up the slogan of \" Hands up ,","depth":9},{"id":256,"text":"don ' t shoot , \"","depth":9},{"id":257,"text":"and led several marches","depth":9},{"id":258,"text":"calling for murder charges to be brought against Officer Wilson .","depth":9},{"id":259,"text":"A few of the marches turned into violent clashes","depth":8},{"id":260,"text":"that destroyed shops and houses .","depth":8},{"id":261,"text":"The response of some police officers , however , renewed fears of law enforcement misconduct .","depth":7},{"id":262,"text":"Pictures from Ferguson repeatedly showed police in full riot gear ,","depth":10},{"id":263,"text":"sometimes armed with Pentagon-issued military weapons such as sniper rifles ,","depth":11},{"id":264,"text":"and accompanied by armored vehicles ,","depth":11},{"id":265,"text":"confronting unarmed groups of protesters .","depth":9},{"id":266,"text":"Several reporters said","depth":10},{"id":267,"text":"they were threatened by police","depth":12},{"id":268,"text":"for trying to record the protests ,","depth":12},{"id":269,"text":"and in one instance a Missouri officer threatened to kill a reporter","depth":12},{"id":270,"text":"if the journalist did not leave the area .","depth":12},{"id":271,"text":"The officer later resigned .","depth":9},{"id":272,"text":"The tensions prompted calls from citizens","depth":6},{"id":273,"text":"to investigate how the police were able to obtain military equipment .","depth":6},{"id":274,"text":"Several members of Congress said","depth":7},{"id":275,"text":"they would support legislation","depth":8},{"id":276,"text":"that would \" demilitarize \" the police .","depth":8},{"id":277,"text":"\" Our main streets should be a place for business , families and relaxation , not tanks and M16s , \"","depth":7},{"id":278,"text":"Rep. Henry C. \" Hank \" Johnson Jr. , a Georgia Democrat , said in a letter to colleagues","depth":8},{"id":279,"text":"seeking support for a bill","depth":9},{"id":280,"text":"that would end programs","depth":10},{"id":281,"text":"that allow the police to buy surplus military equipment .","depth":10},{"id":282,"text":"Though tensions have been high since August ,","depth":7},{"id":283,"text":"the number of rallies , protests and riots declined","depth":8},{"id":284,"text":"as residents waited for the grand jury and federal investigators to finish their reviews .","depth":8},{"id":285,"text":"Mr. Nixon said","depth":9},{"id":286,"text":"he was taking precautions","depth":10},{"id":287,"text":"to stop violence","depth":11},{"id":288,"text":"that may erupt .","depth":11},{"id":289,"text":"\" That ugliness was not representative of Missouri ,","depth":10},{"id":290,"text":"and it can not be repeated , \"","depth":10},{"id":291,"text":"he said recently .","depth":9},{"id":292,"text":"Mr. Nixon ' s decision","depth":10},{"id":293,"text":"to declare a state of emergency , however ,","depth":10},{"id":294,"text":"was met by criticism from some civil rights groups ,","depth":10},{"id":295,"text":"including the NAACP .","depth":10},{"id":296,"text":"\" The more than 200,000 people","depth":12},{"id":297,"text":"who descended on Washington , D.C. , on Aug. 28 , 1963 ,","depth":12},{"id":298,"text":"proved","depth":12},{"id":299,"text":"that protests don ' t need to be violent","depth":13},{"id":300,"text":"to be powerful , \"","depth":13},{"id":301,"text":"the organization said in a press release .","depth":10},{"id":302,"text":"\" From the Boston Tea Party to the Montgomery bus boycotts , the ability","depth":12},{"id":303,"text":"to protest","depth":12},{"id":304,"text":"is woven into the very fabric of our nation","depth":11},{"id":305,"text":"and should not be stifled by presumptuous leadership . \"","depth":10},{"id":306,"text":"Mr. Nixon traveled to St. Louis from the state capital in Jefferson City on Monday","depth":6},{"id":307,"text":"as word leaked","depth":7},{"id":308,"text":"that the grand jury decision was imminent .","depth":7},{"id":309,"text":"- Jennifer Pompi and Ben Wolfgang contributed to this article ,","depth":2},{"id":310,"text":"which is based in part on wire service reports .","depth":2}],"relations":[{"parent":621,"left":619,"right":620,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":619,"left":544,"right":618,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":544,"left":426,"right":543,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":426,"left":328,"right":425,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":328,"left":326,"right":327,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":326,"left":314,"right":325,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":314,"left":313,"right":3,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":313,"left":312,"right":2,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":312,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":325,"left":316,"right":324,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":316,"left":4,"right":315,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":315,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":324,"left":320,"right":323,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":320,"left":319,"right":11,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":319,"left":7,"right":318,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":318,"left":8,"right":317,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":317,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":323,"left":321,"right":322,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":321,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":